# Code and Naming Conventions

- Use English for identifiers: variables, functions, classes, types, file names, flags, env keys.
- Prefer English for code comments in source files; Russian comments are allowed in project docs and task snippets.
- Use Russian only for user-facing error texts and file logs.
- Keep changes surgical; do not refactor unrelated code.
- Respect existing project structure and module boundaries from `cursor.md`.
- Validate changes with relevant checks before finalizing.
